The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in automated cyber response, which falls under the category of AI in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of a simulation and a planner to solve problems, which falls under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of decision theory and cost/benefit tradeoffs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
